vectorData.altText: 5. Which functional fibre types are present in intercostal nerves? Choose all that apply.
That's right!  Intercostal nerves are extensions of the ventral rami, and as such, contain the same fibre types as the ventral rami.

2.1   The Sympathetic Chain in the Thorax

Intercostal nerves, being the continuation of ventral rami, contain sympathetic postganglionic fibres as well as somatic motor and sensory fibres. The sympathetic postganglionic fibres innervate vascular smooth muscle, arrector pili muscle and glands. 
The cell bodies of these sympathetic postganglionic fibres are located in the sympathetic chain ganglia. The connections between the spinal nerves and sympathetic chain are the rami communicantes.
